data.text: Willow Smith became an overnight sensation with “Whip my hair”, Snooki & JWow write an anonymous letter to Sammie to inform her of Ronnie’s indiscretions. Adventure Time is the best cartoon tv show. Batman, Superman, and Wonder Woman are all on a movie screen at the same time .

McDonald's started offering free wifi throughout the USA. A Kansas State University professor went on a Twinkie diet, where he ate Twinkies, Oreos, and Doritos to prove to his students that calorie counting is the important part of losing weight. He lost 27 pounds in 2 months.

Apple released the first iPad. Angry Birds was your favorite app. Train’s “Hey, Soul Sister” was literally everywhere. The Walking Dead show just premiered. Life ended on the island of “Lost” — and continued, for better or for worse, on “Jersey Shore.”

Toy Story 3 was the highest-grossing movie of the year. Flash mobs were a thing. Veronica Roth wrote the first draft of Divergent in 40 days over winter break of her senior year at Northwestern. Lady Gaga wore that meat dress. Everyone was obsessed with Facebook.

Ke$ha's "Tik Tok" was the number one song of the year. Katy Perry's "California Gurls" was the unofficial song of summer. Good Luck Charlie aired its first episode on the Disney Channel. Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows: Part 1 hit theaters.
